# Theme mode (light/dark) requirements

## Must
- The app must support **light and dark** mode across the entire UI.
- Theme mode must be **persisted in `localStorage`** under key `themeMode`.
- Mode must apply globally via a single `ThemeProvider` (no per-page theme providers).
- All background/text/surface colors must come from MUI theme tokens (`theme.palette.*`) so both modes render correctly.

## Never
- Do not hardcode hex colors in components (allowed only inside the theme builder).
- Do not use CSS to set page backgrounds or text colors in a way that conflicts with MUI theme / `CssBaseline`.

## Reference implementation (required shape)
- Theme factory: `src/theme/createAppTheme.js` exporting `createAppTheme(mode)`.
- Provider: `src/theme/ThemeModeProvider.jsx` exporting `ThemeModeProvider` and `useThemeMode()`.

